The Regal movie theater chain has announced the return of its 2022 Regal Summer Movie Express series, where tickets are just $2 on Tuesdays and Wednesdays to see children’s movies. Other theater chains such as AMC and CMX Cinemas (formerly Cobb Theatres) also have done cheap summer family movie series in the past, but they have not yet announced if they will be doing them this summer. Regal will feature kid favorites such as “Despicable Me” and “The Lego Movie” for $2 on Tuesday and Wednesday mornings. The theater says availability varies by location, so check participating theaters for schedules. Tampa Bay area Regal theaters include Regal Park Place & RPX in Pinellas Park, Regal Citrus Park in Tampa, Regal at the Largo Mall and Regal Hollywood in Port Richey. The movie schedule runs now through the end of August. Regal schedule May 31 and June 1: “The LEGO Movie” and “The Penguins of Madagascar” June 7-8: “Dr. Seuss’ The Lorax” and “The LEGO Movie 2: The Second Part” June 14-15: “Abominable” and “The LEGO Batman Movie” June 21-22: “Despicable Me” and “Pokémon Detective Pikachu” June 28-29: “Despicable Me 2″ and “Space Jam” July 5-6: “Puss in Boots” and “Sing” July 12-13: “Sing 2″ and “Space Jam: A New Legacy” July 19-20: “Despicable Me 3″ and “Tom & Jerry” July 26-27: “Minions” and “Trolls: World Tour” Aug. 2-3: “The Boss Baby: Family Business” and “The Croods: A New Age” Aug. 8-9: “How to Train Your Dragon: The Hidden World” and “Trolls” Aug. 16-17: “Scoob!” and “The Secret Life of Pets” Aug. 23-24: “Hop” and “The Secret Life of Pets 2″ Aug. 30-31: “The Grinch” and “Shrek” In 2021, CMX offered $1.50 family movies every Tuesday, Wednesday and Thursday morning as part of its Summer Kids Movies series. Check cmxcinemas.com for any announcements. The AMC Summer Movie Camp in 2021 offered movies and a kids pack of snacks for $4 on Wednesday mornings. Check amctheatres.com for announcements.